HEADWORD: Saddlebags
<hw>Sad"dle*bags</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>Bags, usually
of leather, united by straps or a band, formerly much used by horseback
riders to carry small articles, one bag hanging on each side.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

